FBIS3-35098 "drnes034_r_94006" FBIS-NES-94-034 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Feb 1994 India BJP Assails Clinton Remarks on Rights in Kashmir BK1702154994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 GMT 17 Feb 94 BK1702154994 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The BJP [Bharatiya Janata Party] has criticized President Clinton's statement on human rights in Kashmir and said it violated diplomatic norms. In a statement, the party president, Mr. L.K. Advani, said Mr. Clinton's reference to Kashmir constitutes an unwarranted interference in India's internal affairs. He said the recent statements of U.S. Administration show that it seeks to dismember India. He urged the government to convey the nation's sentiments against such utterances which will embolden terrorists aided by Pakistan.
